- Second derivative: $\partial_t^2 (\cos(\omega t) \cdot x_0 + \sin(\omega t)/\omega \cdot v_0) = -\omega^2 \cos(\omega t) \cdot x_0 - \omega \sin(\omega t) \cdot v_0$

Now, plugging into the equation of motion: $\ddot{x} + \omega^2 x = 0$

